President Barack Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts. These appointments include Jason Glass as a member of the Board of Directors of the National Board for Education Sciences, Susanna Loeb as a member of the Board of Directors of the National Board for Education Sciences, Lesley Israel as a member of the Commission for the Preservation of America's Heritage Abroad, Sheila Lirio Marcelo as a member of the Library of Congress Trust Fund Board, John W. Miller as a member of the Library of Congress Trust Fund Board, Rickey D. James as a commissioner for the Mississippi River Commission, and Rear Admiral Shepard Smith as a commissioner for the Mississippi River Commission. President Obama expressed his gratitude to these individuals for their dedication and willingness to serve the American people.